   "source": [
    "quiz4-q6\n",
    "\n",
    "Define a function that can be called with one or two\n",
    "arguments. If called with two arguments it returns the\n",
    "difference of the first minus the second one. If called\n",
    "with one argument it returns the argument itself"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def myfun(a,b=0):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return a-b\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "1"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "myfun(3,2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

      "text/plain": [
       "3"
      ]

   ]

    "\n",
    "t=[k*2*pi/1000 for k in range(1000)]\n",
    "x=[2*cos(k) for k in t]\n",
    "y=[2*sin(k) for k in t]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(x,y)\n",
    "plt.axis('equal');"

   "source": [
    "### Step 0\n",
    "\n",
    "Given a convergent series (either p-series or geometric)\n",
    "\n",
    "$p=2$, $\\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac{1}{n^2}$\n",
    "\n",
    "* find radius, center (0,0) of the black circle. How to find `R`?  \n",
    "* $A=\\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac{1}{n^p}=\\zeta(2)=1.6...$\n",
    "\n",
    "* $R=\\sqrt{\\frac{A}{\\pi}}$\n",
    "\n",
    " "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy.special import zetac"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 49,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "data": {

     "execution_count": 49,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "1+zetac(2) # sum without n=1 term"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 50,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [

      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 50,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "A=1+zetac(2)\n",
    "R=(A/pi)**0.5\n",
    "R"
   ]

   "source": [
    "### Define a function which will compute all the radii\n",
    "\n",
    "`gen_radii(p,series,N)`\n",
    "\n",
    "* `p` = series parameter\n",
    "* `series` = 'geometric' or 'pseries'\n",
    "* `N` = how many circle\n",
    "\n",
    "output \n",
    "\n",
    "* `R` = radius of big circle\n",
    "* `rlist` = radii of the N small circles"
   ]
  },

   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def myfun(a,b,c):\n",
    "    blist=[a-c,b-c]\n",
    "    return a+b,blist"

    "def gen_radii(p,series,N):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if series == 'geometric':\n",
    "        S\n",
    "        alist \n",
    "    elif series == 'pseries':\n",
    "        S = 1+zetac(p) # sum of conv. p-series\n",
    "        alist\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return 'Series type non-valid'\n",
    "        \n",
    "    R\n",
    "    rlist\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return R,rlist"
   ]

    "\n",
    "colors=[cm.cool((r**-1)%1) for r in rlist]\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1=plt.subplot(1,1,1)\n",

    "\n",
    "for k in range(len(xlist)): \n",

    "plt.axis('equal')\n",
    "plt.xlim([-1.1*R,1.1*R])\n",
    "plt.ylim([-1.1*R,1.1*R])\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
